I’ve been going here since moving to the area. You could call me a regular or at least a frequent patron. However, after tonight, which was the most recent of frustrating experiences of the past year of dining here, I am done. I will not be going back.  Let me be clear, it is the service. Not the food. The food is always excellent and consistent. Plenty of it, good tasting, and delicious. However, the service, of which was very good several years ago has consistently been bad to simply awful over the past year.  The waitstaff, although super friendly, will have to be reminded of simple things - please bring us utensils and napkins, please remember that my child gets a dessert with this meal according to the menu, please can I get a refill of my drink? That is if you can get your waitperson’s attention. Simply put the most frustrating of the dining experience is that after the initial order, you are pretty much abandoned. Every once in a while your waitperson checks on you and since you have been waiting for so long you feel like you are piling on all the requests, some of which should be basic (can I please have a utensil)?  Tonight, after another of what I have come to expect but hope against in the vast wasteland of the back table and forgotten about, my party of five, one being an exhausted child, waited for 25 minutes to get our check. My friend and I got up and walked to the kitchen entrance to find our waitress to ask to please get the check. After waiting for another few minutes, with our coats on ready to go, we asked for the check. This took another ten minutes to receive. To clarify, this now was 35 minutes to get the check after the waitress saw we had put our coats on and had to find her. When she handed us the check, there was no apology, no sense of disregard, and no pen to fill out the tip and total. Luckily, my buddy had a pen otherwise I assume we might have waited until closing time. The kicker was we then had to find the waitress again to simply hand her the now completed check.  First world problems? Yes. Do people deal with much more in the world? Of course. Going out for a nice time for a night of dining and leisure should hopefully be an enjoyable experience. It was due to the company but what was clear is that Margarita’s, what once was my favorite restaurant in town, where I brought friends routinely, was now a place that I will now go out of my way to avoid and that’s sad.

Service is good. Lots of menu options, including a decent block of tasty vegetarian dishes, and other items on the menu marked "can be made vegetarian." Also a la carte options, so if you're torn, for example, between the one of the fish taco entrées and the enchiladas banderas, you get an individual fish taco and the banderas plate, or, the fish taco plate and an individual enchilada. Decent desserts, good for sharing. You'll wanna share because you will be FULL after your meal. Kid friendly, especially on the patio. Full wrap-around bar indoors. TVs to watch the sports games, if that's your thing (it's not mine, as you've probably surmised). Lots of seating indoors, clean restrooms (I can only speak for the ladies'). A fun, tasty place, great to come with a group of friends, large or small.

He approached us and knocked on the window (without identifying himself ) and asked where we were going.  This isn’t normal behavior and I felt really uncomfortable and I phoned the Waltham police.  The officer we spoke to was actually familiar with this guy, because she actually asked him who he was as he was lingering in the parking lot.  Turns out he's a Margarita's employee!! So as we parked in the lot, we went in the restaurant and I told the hostess about the man in the back and suggested he wear a Margarita's shirt so as to not scare other customers away.  As we sat down at the bar, another couple followed behind us and were served immediately with chips and salsa and drinks (while our bartender completely ignored us).  She (The bartender) continued to talk to the other couple in Spanish while we patiently waited for service.  Luckily the other bartender, came by and took our food and drink order.  By the time we got her attention, we quickly ate our food and left after one drink.  I thought bartenders liked to make money!  We won't be back.  Bison country has better food and better service - we kept coming back because we had a lot of good memories there.

Three stars pretty much guarantees that this review will go unread, but here goes.  We've been there a few times, but waited to comment until sure.  Pros: The server was very nice, and the food and drinks did not take that long to come, especially considering the low server to patron ratio. The alcoholic drinks are good, though the strength has varied from visit to visit.  Cons: the food. The fish tacos and other fish dishes were pedestrian, but edible. The regular tacos, though...meh. On the scale from "Taco Bell" to "Cucina Azteca", this leans away from the latter - neither good food nor authentic, kind of the dumbed-down for white people version of ethnic cuisine. Spice, meaning peppery heat, might be ok, but flavor is too scary to consider. Even this we might have been able to look past, but the churros... poorly fried dough, suffocated under sugar so lightly accosted with cinnamon that the color barely changed. The vanilla ice cream seemed to be there to take away some of the sweetness!  That's right - the dessert was nigh inedible.  To be fair, we did go to a chain restaurant, so we shouldn't anticipate haute, or even cuisine, but even with diminished expectations, this was disappointing.

Margaritas in Waltham is one of the few restaurants in the area with outdoor seating. The bar is large too, with friendly bartenders who will happily make your drinks the way you like them (we like our margaritas unsweetened).  If you are vegan, order the gluten-free tortilla chips because they are not fried in shared oil. The vegetarian burrito (without cheese or sour cream) is a good choice. Double check that you get what you ordered as sometimes allergy requests get confused in the kitchen. You can also create a lovely meal out of sides with soft tortillas, rice, refried beans, guacamole, & salsa.  Margaritas is a great place to meet up with friends before a movie or an evening hanging out on Moody St. You can watch the sunset and enjoy a few drinks without feeling claustrophobic in the ample dining room.  Bathrooms are clean. Drinks may come with the occasional fruit fly drowned in it from being attracted by all the citrus (just ask for a new one). Parking isn't easy so be ready for at least a short walk.
